<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-27T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-27T21:00:00-05:00" n="138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">824.24/872: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Boal</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-27T22:00:00-04:00">September 27, 1943—10
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1197. Your 1567, September 22, 7 p.m.<note n="50" xml:id="d138fn50">Not printed; in this telegram the Ambassador reiterated the
                                    preference of the Bolivian Country Agency for Alternative I and
                                    its acceptance of Alternative III only if time were allowed to
                                    apply new import and exchange controls.</note> The Department is
                                making no change in export control procedure as regards Bolivia.
                                Decentralization Plan A will continue for the present in full effect
                                in Bolivia.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>